From 1ca04aa99e49d5df25bec5cfc5e71b675949a28b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Chris Lu <lu@alcg.io>
Date: Fri, 20 Mar 2026 17:02:16 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 05/10] tracer: add cross-OSD span linking and
 BlueStore/replication spans
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Propagate OTEL trace context across OSD sub-operations for both
replicated and erasure-coded pools, enabling end-to-end trace
visibility from primary to replica OSDs.

Wire format changes:
- MOSDRepOp: HEAD_VERSION 3→4, encode/decode otel_trace
- MOSDECSubOpWrite: HEAD_VERSION 2→3, encode/decode otel_trace

Context propagation:
- ReplicatedBackend::issue_op() copies osd_parent_span context
  onto outgoing MOSDRepOp messages
- ECBackend copies osd_parent_span context to EC Op struct,
  ECCommon::finish_writes() sets it on outgoing MOSDECSubOpWrite

New spans:
- queue_transactions: wraps full BlueStore txc lifecycle
  (STATE_PREPARE through STATE_KV_DONE)
- txc_aio_wait: child span capturing async I/O wait time
  (device latency)
- op_commit: fires when all shards have committed in
  ReplicatedBackend

Also adds End() and reset() to noop jspan/jspan_ptr stubs for
non-HAVE_JAEGER builds.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
